<p>Our definition of an exponential function <m>f\left(x\right)={b}^{x}</m> says <m>b&gt;0,</m> but the examples and discussion so far has been about functions where <m>b&gt;1.</m> What happens when <m>0&lt;b&lt;1</m>? The next example will explore this possibility.</p>

